The paper deals with parallel algorithms for a problem that arises in distributed computing, specifically in distributed computer security. This suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) sub-category. The problem involves finding equivalence classes of a set of elements, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. The paper also involves analysis of lower bounds and distribution-based analysis, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-category. Finally, the problem involves pairwise comparison, which is a common technique in cryptography, suggesting that the paper may also belong to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category.
